Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
end_parallel_edit(25.10)                              end_parallel_edit(25.10)

Name
       end_parallel_edit - Ends parallel editing

Syntax
       end_parallel_edit

       [-help]

       -out_file <parallel_edit_file_name>

       Ends parallel editing. The command:

              * compares  the  data  in memory with the original data saved in
                binary files by start_parallel_edit

              * saves the parallel edit file with the specified name

       Multiple end_parallel_edit commands are allowed after one  start_paral-
       lel_edit.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each end_parallel_edit parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man end_parallel_edit

       -out_file <parallel_edit_file_name>
              Specifies the name of the parallel edit file.

Example
              * The  following  command  compares  the data in memory with the
                data saved in the binary files and writes  the  parallel  edit
                information to PE1.txt file:

                innovus 8> end_parallel_edit -out_file PE1.txt

                Start saving parallel edit information to PE1.txt

                ************************************************************************

                Comparing net attribute and regular wire/via with reference DB

                Comparing instance with reference DB

                Comparing physical pin with reference DB

                Comparing NDR rule with reference DB

                Comparing routing blockage with reference DB

                Comparing placement blockage with reference DB

                Comparing via cell with reference DB

                Comparing special wire/via with reference DB

                ************************************************************************

                End saving parallel edit information

Related Information
              *

                read_parallel_edit_files

              *

                start_parallel_edit

              *

                Editing Wires chapter in the User Guide

                * Parallel Editing Capability

